) rendered last. It also adds grouped category headings on the store home “All Products” sec
tion when no category pill is selected and more than 2 categories are present.

Critical findings / analysis:
- `ProductsPageClient.tsx`:
  - Adds `viewMode: "category"` alongside existing grid/list without breaking existing filter/sort/category logic.
  - Category mode renders grouped sections with per-category count and horizontal product rows, satisfying the browse/discovery goal.
  - Uncategorized products are explicitly grouped under `"__other__"` and appended last as “অন্যান্য পণ্য”, matching fallback intent.
- `StoreHomeClient.tsx`:
  - Adds conditional grouped rendering when `!selectedCategory && distinctCategoriesInFiltered.length > 2`, aligning with requirement trigger.
  - Group headings and counts are rendered properly; uncategorized group appears at end.

Comments (non-blocking):
1) In home grouped mode, each category is truncated to `gridCols * 2` products and the prior `showAll` behavior is bypassed in that branch. This may hide products compared to previous “All Products” behavior. If intended, fine; if not, add a per-group “see more” or preserve global expansion behavior.
2) Category ordering differs between pages (home preserves encounter order; products page sorts alphabetically). Not functionally wrong, but consistency may improve UX.

Security: none observed.

Next actions:
1) Confirm intended product visibility on home grouped mode (truncate vs full/per-group expansion).
2) Optionally unify category ordering strategy across home/products grouped views for predictable browsing.
